Therefore, cs.SY (Systems and Control) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also includes an example in the context of robot motion planning, which suggests that it could be classified under cs.RO (Robotics). The paper deals with communication networks, which suggests that it could be classified under cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). The paper also mentions communication constraints and quantization errors, which suggests that it could be classified under cs.IT (Information Theory).
